Yesterday I assigned six hours for practising their songs on my cor anglais, clarinet, E-flat clarinet, bass clarinet and bassoon. I practised with my friends who played triangle, tambourine, castanets, sleigh bells and cymbals, all of which have indefinite pitch. Adding these instruments makes the music more rhythmic. Saxophone, cor anglais and clarinet are transposing instruments. Flute is a reedless instrument. My friend Joe isn't very well-to-do while his girlfriend's family is very well-off. He gave a party yesterday where cheap wines were served. The sofas in his flat are made of some cheap material. He asked me to get him some bach scores as I can get them on the cheap from a friend of mine. We watched a boxing fight where paul hit chris with a cheap shot after he lost to chris. His jokes and jibes were cheap and vulgar.
